GG_ROTARY This is a map I completed a few months back, but I never got around to a public release. Well, here it is! The gameplay is based off of the concept of interlocking circles which rotate in opposite directions at varying speeds. A big thanks to shini for the awesome skybox (Spaced Out). -=Background Information=- A large archaic mechanism in deep space, spinning endlessly for an unknown purpose. Yet there is a purpose for you: kill the enemies in a fast pace game of GunGame while trying to retain your orientation. :::Includes::: - Support for up to 32 Players - Both HDR and non-HDR cubemaps/skybox - A fully-functioning radar/overview - Custom textures All bsp-zipped for easy addition to gameservers!!! NOTE: I'm sure I'll get complaints about it being "too dark". I'd like to make clear that first, its not the lighting but rather my volumetric fog (set at 0 0 0 for black) which is causing this. Secondly, this is to ensure the Gun-Game style play of fast-paced close-combat, not the aim-style of hiding and picking off people at a distance.

The third installment of the gg_rotadome series!
From gg_rotadome_v2: In the dome, there is a circular area in the center, divided by a wall. CT's spawn on one side, T's spawn on the other. On top of the wall sits a small snipers nest, with a ladder leading to it from both sides of the wall. A rotating 'conveyor belt' sort-of thing surrounds the spawn areas. The rotating platform is designed to travel from one spawn area to another, but can be used for drive-bys if you are inclined to do so.
gg_rotadome_v3 updates the previous maps in the series by adding various LDR lighting effects (all static, so don't worry about your FPS), a sunken rotating platform covered with water (44 units high), an open-roofed circular wall surrounding the play area, fixed ladder, increased player limit and more. This is a fun, fast-paced and innovative GunGame map that players will love.

This is my second (technically third) map, gg_rotadome_v2.
It is derived from another map of mine, gg_rotadome, but v2 has a snipers nest in the middle of the map.

In the dome, there is a circular area in the center, divided by a wall. CT's spawn on one side, T's spawn on the other.
On top of the wall sits a small snipers nest, with a ladder leading to it from both sides of the wall.

A rotating 'conveyor belt' sort-of thing surrounds the spawn areas.
The rotating platform is designed to travel from one spawn area to another, but can be used for drive-bys if you are inclined to do so.

I found this layout on the "bottom" of my hard drive and decided to do something with it.

The map name comes from the association of the map colours (Red,Green and Blue) and the RGB color model (name given to the sensing, representation, and display of images in electronic systems, such as televisions and computers)

Added HDR, and buyzones. This is a simple map intended for fast gameplay and fast rounds.

You can jump from almost every part of the map without damage so you can do your favourite Ninja attacks from the sky :D
